 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of the management data that may apply to product data. 
     It brings together modules to provide the ability for other modules to assign 
     management information to product data. Such management data comprises:
     <ul>
	     	<li>dates and times;
	     	</li>
	     	<li>people and organizations;
	     	</li>
	     	<li>approvals;
	     	</li>
		<li>identifiers and aliases for items
		</li>
		<li>certificates and contracts; 
		</li>
		<li>projects;
		</li>
		<li>security classifications.
		</li>
	</ul>
	In some cases these data are also applied to the management data. 
	For example, to specify who specified the security classification for some product data and when, 
	requires the assignment of person and organization, and date and time to the security classification assignment.
   </p>
 </purpose>

